, "name": "A-diagnostics", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2018-03-19T12:36:02Z", "updated_at": "2019-04-29T20:58:27Z", "closed_at": "2019-04-29T20:58:27Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I reduced the code to this:\r\n````rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let greeting = String::from(\"hello world\");\r\n    let mut new = &format!(\"This prints: {}\", greeting).to_string();\r\n    \r\n    // try to push to the str using format\r\n    new.push_str(&format!(\"oh no {}\", \":(\"));\r\n}\r\n````\r\n\r\nwhich gave a quite confusing error message:\r\n````\r\nerror[E0596]: cannot borrow immutable borrowed content `*new` as mutable\r\n --> src/main.rs:6:5\r\n  |\r\n6 |     new.push_str(&format!(\"oh no {}\", \":(\"));\r\n  |     ^^^ cannot borrow as mutable\r\nwarning: variable does not need to be mutable\r\n --> src/main.rs:3:9\r\n  |\r\n3 |     let mut new = &format!(\"This prints: {}\", greeting).to_string();\r\n  |         ----^^^\r\n  |         |\r\n  |         help: remove this `mut`\r\n  |\r\n  = note: #[warn(unused_mut)] on by default\r\n````\r\n\r\nThe error is fixed by removing reference binding from the format when creating \"new\":\r\n````rust\r\n let mut new = format!(\"This prints: {}\", greeting).to_string();\r\n````\r\nIs it possible to add some \"help: remove this '&'\" hint?", "closed_by": {"login": "estebank", "id": 1606434, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2MDY0MzQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1606434?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/estebank", "html_url": "https://github.com/estebank", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/estebank/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/estebank/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/estebank/gist